### Guidelines

- See [Bilingual Documentation Guidelines](docs/BILINGUAL_DOCUMENTATION_GUIDELINES.md) for detailed instructions
- Code examples should remain in English (no translation needed)
- Technical terms can be kept in English or use common Polish translations
- Verify structural consistency using `./scripts/verify_doc_structure.sh` before committing

### Process

1. Write/create English version (`DOCUMENT_NAME.md`)
2. Add language link placeholder: `> ğŸ‡µğŸ‡± **Polish version**: [Title (PL)](DOCUMENT_NAME_PL.md) *(coming soon)*`
3. Translate to Polish (`DOCUMENT_NAME_PL.md`)
4. Update English version link (remove `*(coming soon)*`)
5. Verify consistency with verification script
6. Commit both versions together

